sections.doco:introduction:
In this paper, we consider the equation
\begin{equation}
  u_{yz} = u_{ts} + u_s \, u_{xz} - u_z \, u_{xs}
\label{main}
\end{equation}
with five independent variables $t$, $x$, $y$, $z$, $s$. This equation is a particular case of Manakov--Santini equation,
\cite{ManakovSantini2006,ManakovSantini2014}
and is related to the five-dimensional equation considered in \cite{MartinezAlonsoShabat}, see Remark 1 below.
We find differential coverings,
\cite{KrasilshchikVinogradov1984,KrasilshchikLychaginVinogradov1986,KrasilshchikVinogradov1989},
with non-removable parameters for Equation (\ref{main}) (equations with such coverings are called Lax-integrable).
One of these coverings was found in \cite{ManakovSantini2006} ans used intensively to study Equation (\ref{main}),
see \cite{ManakovSantini2014}.
We demonstrate that two known 4-dimensional Lax-integrable equations
\begin{equation}
  u_{yz} = u_{tx} + u_x \, u_{xy} - u_y \, u_{xx},
  \label{4D_Pavlov_equation}
\end{equation}\begin{equation}
  u_{ty} = u_z \, u_{xy} - u_y \, u_{xz}
  \label{4D_MASh_equation}
\end{equation}
introduced in \cite{FerapontovKhusnutdinova2003} and
\cite{MartinezAlonsoShabat}, respectively, and their coverings with
non-removable parameters are simple reductions of Equation (\ref{main}) and one
of its coverings.  Some 3-dimensional Lax-integrable reductions of
equation (\ref{4D_MASh_equation}) were considered in
\cite{MorozovSergyeyev2014}. We also find two reductions of
Equation (\ref{4D_Pavlov_equation}) to known 3-dimensional Lax-integrable
equations. One of them turns out to be also a reduction
of (\ref{4D_MASh_equation}).
Equation (\ref{main}) has a recursion operator for symmetries,
\cite{MarvanSergyeyev2012}. We demonstrate how to derive this operator from different considerations based on ideas
\cite{Sergyeyev2015}, see also
 \cite{ KrasilshchikKersten1994, KrasilshchikKersten1995, Marvan1995, MalykhNutkuSheftel2004, MorozovSergyeyev2014}.
Also we study the action
of the operator and its inverse.

